spec: multiprocessing_extra163
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html#multiprocessing.pool.Pool

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/pool.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: multiprocessing.pool.Pool async-variant and iterator method qualnames. Pool.apply_async.__qualname__=='Pool.apply_async' (len=16: 'Pool'=4+'.'=1+'apply_async'=11=16); Pool.map_async.__qualname__=='Pool.map_async' (len=14: 'Pool'=4+'.'=1+'map_async'=9=14); Pool.starmap_async.__qualname__=='Pool.starmap_async' (len=18: 'Pool'=4+'.'=1+'starmap_async'=13=18); Pool.imap.__qualname__=='Pool.imap' (len=9: 'Pool'=4+'.'=1+'imap'=4=9); Pool.imap_unordered.__qualname__=='Pool.imap_unordered' (len=19: 'Pool'=4+'.'=1+'imap_unordered'=14=19); qualname length ordering: imap(9) < map_async(14) < apply_async(16) < starmap_async(18) < imap_unordered(19). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "Pool async variant naming conventions: apply_async (len=11: 'apply'=5+'_'=1+'async'=5=11) = sync apply + '_async' suffix; map_async (len=9: 'map'=3+'_'=1+'async'=5=9) = sync map + '_async' suffix; starmap_async (len=13: 'starmap'=7+'_'=1+'async'=5=13) = sync starmap + '_async' suffix; the '_async' suffix (len=6) is consistent across all async variants; the _async suffix converts blocking methods into non-blocking ones returning AsyncResult; Pool.imap (len=4) and Pool.imap_unordered (len=14: 'imap'=4+'_'=1+'unordered'=9=14) are iterator-based lazy methods: they return iterators instead of complete lists, allowing processing before all results are ready. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "Pool method qualname prefix: 'Pool.'=5 ('Pool'=4+'.'=1=5); all qualnames share this 5-char prefix; imap qualname(9) = 5+4=9 (shortest); imap_unordered qualname(19) = 5+14=19 (longest); compare with extra162 sync method qualnames (apply, map, starmap not explicitly listed there); imap.__qualname__=='Pool.imap' (len=9) ties with asyncio.Queue.put/get qualnames (also 9, established in extra163) — coincidental equal length. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

