table multiprocessing_extra163.mp_pool_iterator_method_qualnames:
  description: "multiprocessing.pool.Pool iterator method qualname checks in mppoolimq163 namespace — Pool.imap.__qualname__=='Pool.imap' (len=9: 'Pool'=4+'.'=1+'imap'=4=9; imap(func, iterable, chunksize=1) is a lazy iterator-based map; it returns results as they become available rather than waiting for all to complete; imap is memory-efficient for large iterables; 'imap'=4 gives the shortest Pool qualname in this spec — same length as asyncio.Queue method qualnames put/get(9) from extra163); Pool.imap_unordered.__qualname__=='Pool.imap_unordered' (len=19: 'Pool'=4+'.'=1+'imap_unordered'=14=19; 'imap_unordered'='imap'=4+'_unordered'=10=14; imap_unordered(func, iterable, chunksize=1) is like imap but returns results in any order as they complete rather than input order — faster when result ordering does not matter; imap_unordered qualname(19) is the longest Pool qualname in this spec: imap(9) < map_async(14) < apply_async(16) < starmap_async(18) < imap_unordered(19)); imap_unordered(19) > starmap_async(18) by 1 because 'imap_unordered'=14 > 'starmap_async'=13 by 1; verified with Python 3.14.3"
